node.text:
Topping Tulips via @mikevdwesteringh 🌷🤩 These endless flowers fields are currently a dream itself. When in the Netherlands, you have to visit one of their breathtaking tulip fields. 🌷

Tulip season spans from the end of March until mid May, but the flowers are usually at their finest halfway through April. Witnessing millions of tulips blooming is a dream come true, especially with that colorful varieties from red, pink, white, yellow, and purple. 😍

Travel tip: When in Netherlands pay a visit to Keukenhof, also known as the Garden of Europe, is one of the world's largest flower gardens, situated in the municipality of Lisse, in the Netherlands. According to the official website, Keukenhof Park covers an area of 32 hectares and approximately 7 million flower bulbs are planted in the gardens annually.

📽 @mikevdwesteringh #nature
📍Zeewolde, Netherlands
🎶 Beautiful Mate - Moonman

node.text:
Switzerland's cliff walk is for thrill-seekers only via @michelphotographych 🇨🇭Would you be brave enough to walk through this high walkway suspended from a rocky mountainside, with peak & valley views, accessed by gondola?

About 300 meters long. It takes just 10-15 minutes to walk it in one direction, photo stops included. If you want to walk it both ways, count about half an hour for your visit.

The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. Most of the area is car free, First included. Grindelwald itself can be reached by car, but for nearly all other places you can travel by train and cable cars only.

Travel Tips: The easiest way to get to First Cliff Walk is by taking a 25-minutes gondola ride from Grindelwald to First. From there, it's just a short walk of 5 minutes to the Cliff Walk. You cannot drive up to First by car or by bus and hiking here from Grindelwald would take you several hours.

📽 @michelphotographych #nature
📍Grindelwald, Switzerland
🎶 Ben Pellow - Roslyn

node.text:
A bibliophile's dream via @madelinestraveling 📚 More than 70,000 books make this library in its hall, Admont Abbey Library in Austria a truly a book lover's paradise!

The Admont Abbey Library is an Austria-based monastic library located in Admont, a small town next to the Enns River in Austria, and is attached to the Admont Abbey. Admont Abbey Library is the largest monastic library in the world, and is noted for its Baroque art, architecture and manuscripts.

Tag your book lover's friends!

📽 @madelinestraveling #nature
📍 Admont Abbey Library, Austria
